results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of unlabeled free bicolored trees with n nodes (n >= 1) and k (1 <= k <= n-1, except k=0 or 1 if n=1, k=1 if n=2) nodes of one color and n-k nodes of the other color (the colors are not interchangeable).
reference: R. W. Robinson, Numerical implementation of graph counting algorithms, AGRC Grant, Math. Dept., Univ. Newcastle, Australia, 1978.
link: R. W. Robinson, Rows 1 through 30, flattened
example: K M N gives the number N of unlabeled free bicolored trees with K nodes of one color and M nodes of the other color.
xref: Cf. A329054 (regular array with same data).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Oct 19 2006
